    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="landing-section">
      <div class="landing-section-inner">
        <p class="section-label">Common Questions</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Pricing FAQ</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Is Soleur really free?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. The Soleur plugin is open source and free to install. There is no paid tier, no usage limit on the plugin itself, and no vendor lock-in. You pay only for your Claude usage through Anthropic.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What does Claude cost?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Claude Code requires either an Anthropic API key (pay-per-token, starting at $3/$15 per million input/output tokens for Sonnet) or a Claude Max subscription ($100&ndash;$200/month for heavy usage with higher rate limits). Most solo founders find the API option more cost-effective for moderate usage.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Why is Soleur free when competitors charge $20+/month?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Soleur is built by a solo founder using Soleur itself. The project is open source because the company-as-a-service model works best when the community can extend, audit, and improve the platform. Revenue will come from optional managed services, not from the core plugin.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Will there ever be a paid version?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">The core plugin will remain free and open source. Future paid offerings may include managed hosting, team features, or premium integrations &mdash; but the {{ stats.agents }} agents and {{ stats.skills }} skills you see today will always be free.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

